I think I'm gonna take off.

15:58.157 --> 15:59.181
Hey.

15:59.491 --> 16:01.459
I thought we were gonna follow
those bread crumbs

16:01.560 --> 16:03.391
back to my place, Hansel.

16:03.495 --> 16:06.020
Robin, I don't get the sense
you like being with me.

16:06.131 --> 16:07.393
I like being with you.

16:07.499 --> 16:09.228
Not as much as you like being alone.

16:09.335 --> 16:11.462
You like eating your own food,

16:11.570 --> 16:13.401
sleeping in your own bed,
doing your own crosswords.

16:13.505 --> 16:15.200
Well, who uses ink?

16:16.542 --> 16:17.531
Sorry.

16:17.643 --> 16:19.975
Okay, I'm a bit set in my ways.

16:20.079 --> 16:21.740
That doesn't mean that this won't work.

16:21.847 --> 16:23.838
Actually, it kind of does.

16:24.883 --> 16:26.145
Wait, are we breaking up?

16:26.251 --> 16:28.776
No, we aren't breaking up.

16:29.321 --> 16:31.653
I'm breaking up with you.

16:36.161 --> 16:39.062
<i>TED; And then,</i>
<i>just when I was about to lose hope,</i>

16:44.703 --> 16:46.830
She spent a year in Antarctica
studying penguins.

16:47.906 --> 16:49.874
<i>TED; Kahlúa, Root beer,</i>

16:51.043 --> 16:53.807
<i>Could this penguin be the slutty pumpkin?</i>

17:03.288 --> 17:04.414
Excuse me?

17:04.556 --> 17:05.818
This is gonna sound crazy,

17:05.924 --> 17:08.950
but I met someone up on this roof
four years ago

17:09.060 --> 17:12.997
and they mixed that cocktail,
and they loved penguins.

17:13.766 --> 17:16.098
By any chance, was that you?

17:19.038 --> 17:20.266
It's you.

17:20.506 --> 17:24.464
- Everyone thought I was crazy, but I...
- You are such a loser.

17:25.044 --> 17:27.342
Come on, I came back for you, Ted.

17:27.445 --> 17:31.041
I penguin-suited up
to show you the error of your ways.

17:31.150 --> 17:34.176
And to score Hula Girl's number.
Check and check.

17:34.286 --> 17:35.776
- Unbelievable.
- Yes, it is.

17:38.490 --> 17:39.514
Wait a minute.

17:39.625 --> 17:41.092
You're that lame army guy.

17:41.193 --> 17:44.356
No, no, that's some other guy.
And he was a kick-ass fighter pilot.

17:44.463 --> 17:45.828
I cannot believe I gave you my number.

17:45.931 --> 17:47.023
Yeah, well, you did. Thanks.

17:47.132 --> 17:48.121
Yeah, well, give it back.

17:48.233 --> 17:51.532
Well, I don't think so. I earned it.
Fair and square. I'm calling you.

17:51.670 --> 17:53.968
But I'm never gonna go out with you.

17:54.073 --> 17:57.770
But how will you know it's me?
I'm a master of disguise.

17:58.877 --> 17:59.969
Yeah.

18:00.746 --> 18:01.804
